question.title: How to properly add spring-cloud-gcp-starter dependency in Spring Boot Maven project?
question.body:
How to properly add Google Cloud Storage dependency in Spring Boot Maven project?

I'm trying to integrate Google Cloud Storage into my Spring Boot backend project using Maven, but I'm running into issues.

Here‚Äôs what I tried:

pom.xml snippet:

<dependency>
    <groupId>com.google.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-gcp-starter-storage</artifactId>
</dependency>

But this gives me red highlight error in the IDE saying that it cannot find the artifact.

I also tried adding a version manually, but it still doesn‚Äôt resolve:

<dependency>
    <groupId>com.google.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-gcp-starter-storage</artifactId>
    <version>1.2.8.RELEASE</version> <!-- I tried a few -->
</dependency>

I‚Äôm using:

  • Spring Boot version: 3.4.5
  • Java version: 21
  • Maven in IntelliJ IDEA

What I want to do:

Just connect to Google Cloud Storage, upload or download files from my backend code.

What errors I get:

  • IDE says artifact not found.

  • When running Maven, I get:

    Could not find artifact com.google.cloud:spring-cloud-gcp-starter-storage:jar

What I need:

  • What is the correct dependency to use?
  • Do I need to install or configure anything manually?
  • How can I make this work with Spring Boot 3.x?

Any working setup or step-by-step configuration would be really helpful üôè

Let me know if you want a simpler or shorter version too. Would you like me to post this for you or help tweak it more?
